                " \nWESTERN CAPE LIQUOR AUTHORITY (WCLA)\n ",
                "ADMIN SUPPORT (OFFICE OF THE CEO) \n(6 Months Contract \u2013 Maternity relief)\nComponent: Office of the Chief Executive Officer\nDepartment: Western Cape Liquor Authority Bellville\nReference Number: WCLA 09/2023\n \nRequirements:\n\u2022 NQF 6 Qualification \u2013 Diploma in a relevant field (Administration)\n\u2022 At least 2-4 year\u2019s relevant experience working in an Executive Management Office Environment\n\u2022 Computer literate with touch-typing skills\n \nExperience and competencies which will be advantageous:\n\u2022 Document Management System experience (advantageous)\n\u2022 Code B Driving license with no vehicle restrictions (advantageous)\n \nKey performance areas:\n\u2022 Provide daily Secretarial and Receptionist support services to the Office of the CEO:\n\u27a2 Responsible for answering all incoming calls in a polite and professional manner.\n\u27a2 Responsible for making outgoing calls as and when necessary.\n\u27a2 Ensuring all emails are acknowledged and responded to in a timely manner.\n\u27a2 Responding to internal and external stakeholders relating to enquiries in a timely manner.\n\u27a2 Responsible for all logistical arrangements of meetings.\n\u27a2 Ensure timely preparation and processing of meeting Agenda\u2019s.\n\u27a2 Provide comprehensive minutes after each meeting.\n\u2022 Rendering Administrative Support Services to the Office of the CEO, the Governing Board and Management Team.\n\u27a2 Ensuring incoming documents is registered and processed timely.\n\u27a2 Drafting of submissions, presentations and conduct relevant research as required.\n\u27a2 Budget Monitoring for the Office and ensuring completion and submission of requisitions\n\u27a2 Processing travel arrangements for the Governing Board, Chief Executive Office, and Management\n\u27a2 Ensuring timely arrangements for catering services\n\u2022 Provide an accurate and up to date record-keeping system:\n\u27a2 Record-keeping of documents in electronic and hard copy formats.\n\u27a2 Record-keeping of all recordings of meetings.\n\u27a2 Record-keeping of all enquiries and responses to the Office of the CEO.\n\u2022 Diary Management of the Chief Executive Officer\n\u27a2 Scheduling all meetings of the CEO and preventing conflicts.\n \nSkills:\n\u2022 Computer literacy plus advanced proficiency in MS Office.\n\u2022 Must be able to do speed typing.\n\u2022 Good verbal communication and interpersonal skills.\n\u2022 Excellent organizing and document management skills.\n \n \nNote: Only shortlisted applicants will receive further correspondence. If you have not received a response from the entity within three months of the closing date, please regard your application as unsuccessful.\n \nShortlisted candidates will be required to submit originally certified copies of their documentation for verification purposes. These candidates will be required to attend interviews on a date and time as determined by the entity and may also be required to undergo competency assessments/ proficiency tests.\n \nThe Western Cape Liquor Authority is guided by the principles of Employment Equity. All candidates invited for interviews may be subjected to competency test/practical tests as part of the interview process. Kindly note that all personal information provided with your application will be dealt with for the intended purpose.\n \nAll completed applications (WCLA Application Form, CV\u2019s and Copies of Qualifications) must be submitted via the following e-mail address: hr@wcla.gov.za\n \nOnly applications submitted via the above-mentioned e-mail address will be accepted\n \nSALARY: R277 059 per annum (Cost to Employment)\nSALARY LEVEL: 5\n \nCLOSING DATE: 20 October 2023\n \nENQUIRIES: Mrs. S Langeveldt: (021) 204 9730 / 92",
                "FINANCIAL MANAGER\nComponent: Finance\nDepartment: Western Cape Liquor Authority (Bellville)\nReference Number: WCLA 12/2023\n \nRequirements:\n\u2022 Bachelor\u2019s Degree (BCom) \u2013 NQF 7 (Degree in Finance with Accounting as a major)\n\u2022 At least 3-5 Years relevant management experience\n\u2022 At least 3-5 Years relevant working experience in a Finance environment\n\u2022 Accounting Background required\n\u2022 Experience on CASEWARE\n\u2022 Experience in GRAP\n\u2022 Experience in Accounting Systems (Pastel or related)\n\u2022 Valid Driver\u2019s License (no vehicle restrictions)\n \nExperience and competencies which will be advantageous:\n\u2022 NQF 8 qualification in Finance or related field (advantageous).\n\u2022 Project management experience (advantageous).\n\u2022 Experience working in/or with the public sector/regulatory framework (advantageous)\n \nKey performance areas:\n\u2022 Reporting\n\u27a2 Compile interim and annual financial statements, statistical reports and statutory reports.\n\u27a2 Administer financial reporting requirements and procedures.\n\u27a2 Compile the quarterly in-year monitoring (IYM) report.\n\u27a2 Prepare ad hoc financial reports on request.\n\u27a2 Prepare monthly management reports including variance analysis.\n\u27a2 Design reports and templates to enhance reporting.\n\u27a2 Provide inputs into the Annual Performance Plan, Annual Financial Statements and Annual Report.\n\u27a2 Address audit issues related to Management Accounting.\n\u2022 Budget (Main and Adjustment)\n\u27a2 Manage and administer demand management and logistics processes and procedures.\n\u27a2 Compile and manage the main and the adjustment budget processes, roll-overs and revenue retention.\n\u27a2 Create and maintain financial databases to support costing, planning and reprioritization.\n\u27a2 Load the approved budgets onto the Pastel accounting system.\n\u27a2 Liaise with the system controller on the creation of new code structures on Pastel.\n\u2022 Expenditure and Revenue Management\n\u27a2 Monitor expenditure and revenue against budget and facilitate remedial measures if necessary.\n\u27a2 Verify budget availability and allocations for all purchases.\n\u27a2 Analyse expenditure and revenue regularly to ensure correct classifications and rectify if required.\n\u2022 Financial Administration\n\u27a2 Maintain general ledger structure.\n\u27a2 Provide required information for internal and external audit.\n\u27a2 Manage cash and bank functions.\n\u27a2 Maintain the administration of the banking system.\n\u27a2 Financial input into payroll function.\n\u27a2 Ensure the recording, authorisation and proper execution of expenditure and revenue systems, procedures and systems.\n\u27a2 Maintain financial system.\n\u27a2 Provide relevant training to staff when required.\n\u27a2 Oversee the petty cash function.\n\u2022 Effective resource management (human, financial and physical) within the Unit\n\u27a2 Establish and maintain appropriate systems (analytical tools, information systems, projections of cost behaviour) and policies to ensure effective and efficient management of resources.\n\u27a2 Perform accurate forecasting, budgeting, and allocation of resources within the unit.\n\n\u27a2 Manage external contractors and suppliers within the unit.\n\u27a2 Develop and manage internal service level agreements with other units.\n\u27a2 Ensure effective identification and management of business risks, resources, and continuous improvement.\n\u27a2 Manage capacity within the unit to ensure sustained service delivery.\n\u2022 Effective people management within the Unit\n\u27a2 Manage people development in line with organisation-wide skills development strategy within the unit.\n\u27a2 Manage talent within the unit and ensure talent management strategies (attraction, retention, development) are implemented.\n\u27a2 Implement performance management within the unit in line with Human Resources Policies and Guidelines.\n\u27a2 Manage grievances, discipline, and terminations within the division in line with Human Resources policies and guidelines.\n\u27a2 Lead and direct staff within the unit to be able to meet the objectives set for them.\n\u27a2 Build and foster a culture of good governance, customer service, honesty and integrity and world class delivery in the division.\n\u27a2 Implement innovative recognition and reward systems.\n\u2022 Effective promotion and practice of good corporate governance, risk and compliance pertaining to HR and financial policies, legislations, and regulations\n\u27a2 Implement governance framework to ensure professional conduct by Unit employees and upholding of WCLA values and governing principles.\n\u27a2 Ensure good governance within the unit in line with the corporate governance guidelines and related legislation.\n\u27a2 Manage risks within the unit.\n\u27a2 Manage compliance within legislation, regulations, WCLA policies and procedures within the unit.\n\u27a2 Ensure compliance of the unit with all audit requirements emanating from audit processes within the unit.\n\u27a2 Draft and submit annual, quarterly, and monthly reports required or delegated.\n \nKnowledge:\n\u2022 Practical implementation experience and working knowledge in generally accepted accounting principles such as IFRIS, GAAP and GRAP\n\u2022 Working knowledge of relevant Public Sector legislation, e.g. PFMA, National and Provincial Treasury Regulations, Administrative Law.\n\u2022 Working knowledge of relevant industry legislation and regulations, e.g. Western Cape Liquor Act, POPI, PAJA, PAIA.\n \nSkills:\n\u2022 High level of report writing skills\n\u2022 Strong analytical and problem-solving skills.\n\u2022 Ability to thrive in a fast-paced environment managing multiple projects and tight deadlines.\n\u2022 Exceptional interpersonal, communication, writing, reporting and presentation skills.\n\u2022 Ability to function independently, within a team and transversally across the organisation\n\u2022 Ability to prioritize and adapt, managing multiple projects and tight deadlines.\n\u2022 Computer literacy plus advanced proficiency in MS Office (Word, Excel, PowerPoint)\n \n \nPlease Note: Only shortlisted applicants will receive further correspondence. If you have not received a response from the entity within three months of the closing date, please regard your application as unsuccessful.\nApplicants must submit a formal WCLA Application form, a comprehensive CV, certified copies of qualifications, identity document and driver\u2019s license (where applicable). Incomplete applications will not be considered.\n \nApplications must be submitted electronically preferably as one PDF document to hr@wcla.gov.za.\nWCLA Application forms can be obtained from the WCLA website: www.wcla.gov.za and must reach the Human Resources Section on or before the closing date indicated. Applicants must clearly state the reference number and position title in the subject line of the e-mail. Only Electronic applications will be accepted.\n \nPlease note that the following will lead to disqualification of applications:\n1. Submission of fraudulent qualifications and / or documentation.\n2. Non-submission of certified copies of academic qualifications / records.\n3. Non-submission of WCLA Application form, Identity document and Driver\u2019s License (where applicable).\n \nShortlisted candidates will be subjected to a vetting process. By applying for this position, candidates agree to reference checks, criminal and qualification checks being performed.\nThe WCLA reserves the right not to make an appointment.\nThe Western Cape Liquor Authority is guided by the principles of Employment Equity. All candidates invited for interviews may be subjected to competency test/practical tests as part of the interview process. Kindly note that all personal information provided with your application will be dealt with for the intended purpose.\nOnly applications submitted via the above-mentioned e-mail address will be accepted.\n \nSALARY: R581 022\u2013 R680 160 per annum (Cost to Employment)\nSALARY LEVEL: 9\n \nCLOSING DATE: 20 October 2023\n \nENQUIRIES: Mrs. S Langeveldt: (021) 204 9730 / 92 / 32"
