                " \nADMINISTRATION ASSISTANT (FINANCE) \n(FIXED TERM CONTRACT UP TO 31 MARCH 2030) \nLOCATION: GAUTENG \nReporting to the Finance Accountant the incumbent in this position will provide support and functional finance administration in support of the finance deliverables. For organisational continuity. The Administrator Assistant will lead the continuous sustainability, and coordinate audit requirements in the Finance unit as the CHIETA core function as part of an integrated operational business process and value chain within the organization. The sustained good performance of the CHIETA is strongly aligned to an effective and efficient Finance unit. \n \nQualifications requirements: \nA minimum of a National Certificate in Finance or Accounting and preferred NQF 6 (Diploma) in Finance/ Accounting/ Auditing or related. \n \nExperience requirements: \nMinimum of 1 to 2 years\u2019 experience within an administration/records management environment. \n \nSkills & Behavioral competencies: \nPlanning and organisation skills\nCommunication (oral and written)\nProblem solving ability\nDiversity awareness\nConfidentiality, ethics, integrity and professionalism\nDetail orientation\nTeamwork Excellent stakeholder engagement skills\n \nKey performance areas: \nAttending to stakeholder queries \nSupplier payments \nSupplier reconciliation \nRecord keeping",
                "Interested persons are invited to submit their CV\u2019s to recruitment@Chieta.org.za\n \nShould no feedback be forthcoming by 30 October 2023, please accept that your application was not successful. The CHIETA reserves the right to not make an appointment. CHIETA is committed to the advancement of Employment Equity. Successful applicants will be subjected to background checks and to undertake required assessments. \n \nClosing date: 23 October 2023.\n \nProtection of Personal Information \u2013 Employment Candidates \n1.              CHIETA is a responsible party in terms of the POPI Act of 2013. \n\n2.              CHIETA will take all prescribed and reasonable precautions to ensure that your information is safeguarded. \nBy submitting your Curriculum Vitae and any other relevant personal information in respect of this vacancy, you understand and agree that: CHIETA needs to collect, keep and use your personal information in order to evaluate your application for purposes of potential employment opportunities; and \nCHIETA will only use the information to carry out the necessary recruitment related activities. \nYou therefore give your consent to CHIETA to process your information knowing all of the above and being aware that you can: Withdraw consent at any time. \nHave the right to request access to your data at any time, in the prescribed form. \nHave a right to request that your data is corrected and updated, in the prescribed form; and \nHave the right to complain to the information regulator. \n \nCHIETA reserves the right not to make an appointment."
